Event List.Event Name: Mortimer comes to Holmes and Watson
Event List.Event Description:
- Dr. Mortimer comes to the house and tells Holmes and Watson of the tale of the Hound of the Baskervilles.

- He tells them how Sir Hugo and Sir Charles Baskerville died.

- He also tells them since Sir Charles died that the heir was Sir Henry Baskerville.

- Sir Henry came the next day at breakfast time. He was staying in he Northumberland Hotel.

-Sir Henry receives a mysterious letter addressed to his hotel. He said that no one could have known.

-The letter said "As you value your life or your reason keep away from the moor."

- The letter was made by pasting words from a newspaper article. The only word in ink was moor.

-They found out that the words were all cut out from a segment of the Times newspaper.

- Holmes and Watson decide to follow Mortimer and Sir Henry to see if they are being followed. When they do this, they find a man inside a cab that is following Mortimer and Sir Henry. The man has a bushy black beard and piercing eyes, but Holmes thinks it is a false one. Holmes gets the license plate number and gets to talk to the driver, but he finds out nothing of importance.

-Holmes and Watson decide to send Barrymore, the Baskerville's butler, a telegram to see if he is actually in London and he is not the man in the cab. They get a telegram that said "Have just heard that Barrymore is at the hall." Therefore, they still don't have a lead.

-Holmes tells Cartwright, his assistant, to visit 23 hotels to get a trace cut sheet of the Times newspaper, but he was unable to find one. All of Holme's & Watson's leads are gone.

-The Notting Hill Murderer, Seldon, is an escaped convict and was living on the moor. Watson discovers that Mrs. Barrymore is his sister, and her and Mr. Barrymore have been giving him the things he needs. They gave him some of Sir Henry's clothes.

-Mr. & Miss Stapleton of Meripit House are neighbors of Baskerville Hall. Mr. Stapleton comes to Baskerville Hall to introduce himself to Watson and asks him about any ideas he has about Sir Charles' death. He also tells him that they moved here shortly after Sir Charles settled there.

-Stapleton tells Watson of the Grimpen Mire, where a "false step yonder means death to man or beast." Stapleton tells him that he has found out paths to take to get out of it.

-Beryl, Stapleton's sister, tells Watson to leave the moor and go straight back to London, thinking that she was Sir Henry. She says she cannot explain, but it is for his own good.

Event List.Event Name: Barrymore, Sir Charles' Letter, and Laura Lyons
Event List.Event Description:
-Watson finds Barrymore at the window with a candle, possibly signaling someone.

-Mr. and Mrs. Barrymore reveal that Mrs. Barrymore found a letter written to Sir Charles asking to meet. The letter asked him to meet at the gate by where on the night of his death. The initials at the bottom of the letter were L.L.

-Watson tracks down Laura Lyons and she says that she did write the letter, but she never met with Sir Charles that night.
